          {
            "text": "Katy, TX has a wide range of highly-rated medspas and facial clinics offering dermaplaning, often paired with custom facials or chemical peels for a \"glass skin\" finish.\n\nBelow are the top-rated locations for a dermaplaning facial in Katy, categorized by their specialties and pricing.\n\n### **Top-Rated MedSpas for Dermaplaning**\n\n*   **Face to Face Spa (Cinco Ranch)**\n    *   **Highlights:** A popular choice for medical-grade facials. They often offer a \"New Client Special\" (approx. $149) that includes a 60-minute Medi-Facial. Dermaplaning is a featured add-on or standalone service here.\n    *   **Location:** 27131 Cinco Ranch Blvd, Suite 750\n    *   **Best for:** First-time clients looking for a high-end introductory deal.\n*   **Katy Medi Spa**\n    *   **Highlights:** Physician-led and highly rated for clinical results. Their dermaplaning treatment is specifically designed to prep the skin for better absorption of their medical-grade serums.\n    *   **Best for:** Those who want a medical environment and customized skincare plans supervised by a doctor.\n*   **MedSpa at Villagio**\n    *   **Highlights:** A \"one-stop-shop\" for beauty. They use a 10-gauge sterile scalpel at a 45-degree angle for precise exfoliation. They are known for being inclusive of all skin types, including darker skin tones where dermaplaning can help reveal a more radiant glow.\n    *   **Location:** 22756 Westheimer Pkwy (Villagio Town Center)\n*   **LUXE Medical Aesthetics**\n    *   **Highlights:** Consistently one of the highest-rated medspas in the area. They specialize in \"The Luxe Effect,\" combining dermaplaning with custom facials for a luxury experience.\n    *   **Location:** 21770 Kingsland Blvd\n*   **Anita Skin Care Clinic**\n    *   **Highlights:** Known for a holistic approach. They often bundle dermaplaning with oxygen infusion or hydro-dermabrasion for an extra hydration boost.\n    *   **Best for:** Affordable pricing and personalized, less corporate atmosphere.\n\n### **Typical Pricing in Katy**\n*   **Standalone Dermaplaning:** $75 – $125\n*   **Dermaplaning Facial (Combo):** $150 – $240\n*   **Membership Pricing:** Many spots like **Restore Hyper Wellness** or **Face to Face Spa** offer member rates. For example, Restore charges approximately **$190 for members** and **$240 for retail** for a 75-minute Custom Facial + Sonic Dermaplaning.\n\n### **Treatment Combinations to Consider**\nIf you are looking for maximum results, ask about these \"Katy-favorite\" pairings:\n1.  **Dermaplaning + Chemical Peel:** The blade removes the \"peach fuzz\" and dead cells first, allowing the peel to penetrate deeper for a more effective glow.\n2.  **Dermaplaning + HydraFacial:** A common \"Red Carpet\" treatment that results in extremely smooth, hydrated skin.\n3.  **Dermaplaning + Oxygen Facial:** Great for a pre-event glow to plump and hydrate the skin immediately.\n\n### **Quick Tips for Your Visit**\n*   **New Client Specials:** Always check the website or call to ask if they have a first-time guest discount; many Katy spas offer 20-50% off your first session.\n*   **Post-Care:** Avoid direct sun exposure for 48-72 hours after your facial, as your skin will be extra sensitive to UV rays.\n*   **Booking:** Most of these locations (especially LUXE and Face to Face) allow for easy online booking via their websites or the Mindbody app.",
            "thoughtSignature": ""
          }
        ],
